{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Code Quality Analyzer",
  "description": "Monitors source code files for changes and provides intelligent suggestions for code improvements, including identifying code smells, recommending design patterns, and highlighting best practices for readability, maintainability, and performance",
  "version": "1",
  "when": {
    "type": "fileEdited",
    "patterns": [
      "**/*.py",
      "**/*.rs",
      "**/*.ts",
      "**/*.tsx",
      "**/*.js",
      "**/*.jsx"
    ]
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Analyze the modified code files for potential improvements. Focus on:\n\n1. **Code Smells**: Identify anti-patterns, duplicated code, long methods/functions, complex conditionals, and poor naming\n2. **Design Patterns**: Suggest appropriate design patterns that could improve the code structure\n3. **Best Practices**: Check for language-specific best practices (Python PEP 8, Rust idioms, TypeScript/React patterns)\n4. **Readability**: Evaluate code clarity, documentation, and maintainability\n5. **Performance**: Identify potential performance bottlenecks and optimization opportunities\n6. **Security**: Flag potential security issues or vulnerabilities\n7. **Testing**: Suggest areas that need better test coverage\n\nFor each file changed, provide:\n- Specific line numbers or code sections that need attention\n- Clear explanation of the issue\n- Concrete suggestions for improvement with code examples where helpful\n- Priority level (Critical, High, Medium, Low)\n\nMaintain the existing functionality - only suggest improvements, not breaking changes. Be constructive and educational in your feedback."
  }
}